The South African national team coach Stuart Baxter said on Thursday that he is looking for continuity in the Bafana Bafana squad.Stuart Baxter said this while announcing the squad that will face Nigeria next month for their 2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers.&#8220;I am looking for some continuity, time has been invested into the players that have been selected previous to me arriving, it&#8217;s important that we don&#8217;t just throw the baby out of the bath water we have got to really try to get some continuity,&#8221; said BaxterBaxter, who will be in charge of the national team for the first time since his announcement, has named the squad to face Nigeria in the opening match of the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers with a few additions.However, the coach added that he has selected the squad with a view of development. &#8220;I am quite pleased with the squad we have assembled. We have a small element of development with a couple of young players. We also have some players who are returning to the squad,&#8221; he said.The coach says that he is preparing hard and ready to face Nigeria. &#8220;I have had three days away from Supersport, I put my Bafana hat on,I have gained a lot of intelligence on Nigeria &#8230; I have got the coach&#8217;s background,&#8221; said BaxterMaking a comeback to Bafana is goalkeeper Ronwen Williams, Bongani Zungu and Tokelo Rantie.A full squad is expected to assemble for camp on June 4 and commerce with training sessions.The 2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers clash will be at the Godswill Akpabio International Stadium in Uyo State, Nigeria on June 10, kick-off at 5pm .-TNA Reporter 